Full sun following morning rain shower.  Swimming not desirable due to abundance of weeds.
Full sun.  Some algae bloom.  Not exact site of a first test.
Bright- sunny.  Light algae bloom on surface.
Clear skies.  Strong north winds.  Lake very choppy.
Public perception due to many weeds.  Bright sunny day.  Pollen off trees has disappeared from lake surface following storms the past two days.
Bright day.  Heavy pond weed growth across lake.  Constant rains past 5 days.
Bright cloudless skies-pond weeds dying off.
Clear + sunny.  Some pollen washed into lake from heavy rainfall.
Clear skies.  Lake churned up from strong NE winds past 2 days.
Clear skies- water level 8" above normal.
Cloudless skies- water level 3" above normal.
Clear skies. Significant pond weed growth. A pair of mute swans came to the lake yesterday. They are feeding on pond weeds.
Clear skies- mild winds. Lake clarity cloudy due to heavy rains this past week.
Bright sun after 5 days of rain. Clarity impaired by run off. fishing poor.
Sunny. Heavy weed growth + algal blooms. 5 days since last rain.
Ice off 4/27.  Rain last night.  Partly cloudy- gusty winds.
Bright sunny day.  Water exceptionally clear.
5 inches of rain on 5/11- lake level over banks for a
Pine pollen of surface in calm bays- few insects-
Bright sun-3/4 " rain of 6/10- many blue heron on

column1: lakeshore- some heron hunting on land for red squirrels. First fawn seen

column2: Cloudy + Cool-NE winds-3 fawns chasing around cabin
Bright Sun- temps in mid-80's- some pollen on surface
Bright sun- Temp. 69 degrees- weeds subsiding
Bright Sun- Lake turned over- water exceptionally
Bright sun. Tem 68 degrees. Beautiful day.
Opening of fishing season.  Bright sun.
Water exceptionally clear.  No significant rain in 3 weeks.  Some rotted weeds on surface on South end of lake.
Slight overcast.  Many weeds on surface.
Weed growth covers 70% of the lake surface.  Lake clarity remains unusual in the past 11 years.  Very hot.
Bright sun.  Considerable runoff from rain storms.
Bright sun.  Ten Canada geese on lake.
Bright sun.  Very windy.  Trees beginning to show a little color.
Weeds beginning to die off.  Rain runoff improved lake level.  Unusually hot for this time.
Brackish color.  Possible result of runoff from considerable rainfall.
Bright sun.  Very dry.  No measurable rain in 3 weeks.
Bright sun.  Cold winds out of the north.
Bright sun.  Many weeds on surface.
High water due to heavy rainfall and beaver dam on Little Portage Creek.  Some weeds are dying off.  Bright sun.
Bright sun.  Weeds sying off and on surface.  Some pollen on surface also.
Unusually clear.  Lake apparently flushed after beaver dam removal.
Bright sun- high lake level over shoreline banks and piers. Has dropped since breaking up beaver dam.
Sunny- few clouds. 84 F. Saw heron and fish jumping.
Bright sun. Many weeds. Pair of Canada geese and 5 goslings now on pier and shoreline. Very little rain over past two weeks.
No testing in past several weeks because of illness. Beavers active in controlling lake level. No rain for several weeks. Lack of pond weeds this year.
Beaver keeping water level high despite lack of rain. Received .5 inches of rain last night but drought continues.
Beaver dam maintaining a high lake level. One of the few lakes in the area not suffering from a major drop in lake level. Bright sun. Some leaves are turning.
Overcast and cool. Probably last reading of year. Dock and boat stored for winter.

First reading of 2008- Ripped out beaver dam May 4 and cleared culvert of debris. Lake level was 15 over shoreline bank. water has reced and level dropped 1.5 feet. Poor lake clarity possibly due to sediment being washed into lake from flooding of shoreline.
Bright sun. Water clarity improved since removal of beaver dam. Lake level dropped 1.5 feet.
cloudy- cold (48 F). Saw 1 eagle- 1 crane on shore.
Partly Sunny. Lake level stabilized after insertion of beaver pipe at dam.
Blue sky- few clouds (65 F). Bullfrogs on shore.

Bright sun.Checked beaver pipe and found water flow hampered by large rock in opening and log and smaller rocks inside pipe. Removed to restore water flow. Pipe appears to maintain lake lievel when not blocked. Beavers are active and have damed entire creek.
Bright sun. Very dry. Lake level approx. 6 inches low. Beaver pipe maintaining lake level stability.
Cloudy before the rain started. No activity on lake- no wildlife.
Lake level high due to rain. Beaver pipe appears to be working well.
First reading of 2009. Clear but windy. Loon on the lake.
Bright sun. Lake level normal due to re-piling of rocks in culvert. Pine pollen on lake surface.
Sunny. Lake level maintaining at optimum height.
Lake cloudy. Received over 3 inches of rain during the week. Lake finally receding after cleaning out baaver pipe.
Bright  sun. Unusually warm. No rain for at least 3 weeks
First reading of year. Lake level has been normal throughtout Winter + Spring- Lake unusually clear. Bright sun.

Over 5 inches of rain on the 20th. Lake over bank extending 20 feet. Flooding on Yellow Brick road. Water running over beaver dam and beaver pipe working well. Water has receded about 4inches to date. Lake level still 1 foot over normal. Water very murky from runoff.
Bright Sun. Lake level high due to 2 plus inches of rain on W4ednesday 9/15/10
Last reading for year. Pier and boats stored for season. Partailly sunny.
cloudy- light wind- 2" rain on 6/21- 1" rain on 6/22
Overcast. Lake level has receded after center portion of dam was opened. Beaver pipe obstructed.
particulates in water- cloudy- calm- 58 degrees- dry- have seen osprey and herons lately
overnight rain 1/4"- sunny wind west 5-15 mph 68 degrees
cold front- partly sunny- 51 degrees- wind from the N.W. 10-15 mph- not too much milfoil
48 degrees- partly sunny- strong wind- last 4 days 25 mph - today 5-10 mph
Bright sun. Beavers have apparently relocated elsewhere as outlet channel has been open all winter- Water clarity seems improved. Canada geese have adopted our property to raise six goslings-
Overcast. Calm water. Very clear. Moderate aquatic plant growth.
Bright sun. Lake level high due to over 6.5 inches of rain during the week.
Sunny. 78 degrees. No wind. Algae suspended. Moderate aquatic plant growth.
Bright sun. Lake level back to normal. Heavy weed growth with algae and pollen.

column1: Pleasant day with mild wind and low humidity.

column2: Bright sun. Windy.Lake clarity unusually cloudy.
Overcast. Very brown murky water. Calm. Milfoil growing.
Bright sun. Temps at 78. Light wind. Lake weedy and cloudy
Ice  out May 22nd. Lake level very high. No apparent obstructions of water flow in outgoing creek. Partly sunny today.
Lake level high. Clarity has improved since last reading.
Lake level very high due to heavy rains. No obstructions visible in outgoing stream. Bright sun!.
Bright sun. Lake level very high- flooding along shoreline. Little Portage Creek free of obstructions. Heavy weeds.

This is the last reading for 2013 as I will be removing my pier and winterizing my boat- Lake level seems high as compared to levels at this time in prior years. Rocks piled in culvert are preventing outflow of water.
First reading of the year. Late ice out. Outboard motor not working. Finally fixed.

column1: Lake level extremely high at ice out. Extensive flooding in lower lake shore elevations. Rocks piled in culvert causing problem. Relocated about five boulders in dam to lower lake level. Lake is now within its banks. Periodic rainfall is maintaining a constant lake level.

column2: Bright sun. Cool. Significant rain over the past two weeks. Lake level remains constant.
partly cloudy; 56 deg F air temp; water very murky in appearance
Partial clouds. Lake choppy. High winds the past few days.
clear; 72 deg F air temp; light breeze
75 F- partly cloudy- eagles on lake 75 F- partly cloudy- eagles on lake
Partly Cloudy- 64 F- Windy 15 mph- was windy last 3 days.
